    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-27T15:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-27T15:42:00-05:00" n="894"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d894">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/263</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">DeBillier</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-27T16:00:00-04:42">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s March 23, 7 p.m. Given positive assurances orally that no
                    distinction will be made between Dutch boats and those referred to in Embassy’s
                    despatch No. 247, October 12, 1917. Promised confirmatory note tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">DeBillier</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
